SENATE CHAMBER
STATE OF OKLAHOMA DISPOSITION
FLOOR AMENDMENT No. ________
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
(Date)
I move to amend House Bill No. 3015 on Page 7, Line 18 1/2, by inserting a new Section 12 to read
as follows, by amending the title to conform, and renumbering subsequent section:
“SECTION 12. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified in the Oklahoma Statutes
as Section 6-110.6 of Title 47, unless there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
A. Whenever an applicant for a driver license or state-issued identification card presents an
original or certified birth certificate copy as proof of identity, Service Oklahoma shall query the
Electronic Verification of Vital Events (EVVE) system prior to issuance of a new driver license or
state-issued identification card, a renewal of a driver license or state-issued identification card, or an
application for a lost or destroyed driver license or state-issued identification card. In the event that
the EVVE system is unable to verify the original or certified birth certificate copy presented for any
reason, the EVVE system shall provide a question-and-answer-based verification process that, with
near certainty, can establish the validity of the professed identity of the applicant.
B. Service Oklahoma shall promulgate rules for the provisions provided for in this section.”
